Rodong Sinmun on Unique Idea and Theory in Socio-Class Relations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 13 (KCNA) -- A major characteristic in socio-class relations at present is that a big change has taken place in the position and role played by social communities in the process of the development of the times and history, says Rodong Sinmun Friday in a signed article.
 This big change can be explained by the fact that the revolutionary army has emerged the driving force and the core force of the revolution, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The working class has played a role as the driving force of the revolution in the past. But the times have advanced and socio-historical conditions have changed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The working class today is fundamentally different from that in the period of industrial capitalism and proletarian revolution in view of the environment of the times, labor and social position of the working class and the actual situation of the working class movement today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary army has the highest revolutionary and militant spirit and the strongest sense of organization than any other group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean People's Army is the most revolutionary, militant and strongest revolutionary group in our society. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present reality clearly proves that no force can replace the revolutionary army in its might as it takes the lead in foiling the imperialists' aggression and war policy and brings about social progress and the independent development and prosperity of the country and the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Another major characteristic of the socio-class relations at present is that the confrontation and struggle between socialism and capitalism and between independent forces and dominationist forces have become fiercer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The class contradiction has not weakened but grown more acute in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists have become keener on aggression overseas as the inflation of monopoly capital gets worse and their state political and socio-economic systems turn more reactionary and militaristic. They are, therefore, resorting to high-handed and arbitrary practices on the international arena and in every part of the world while viciously pursuing the policy of aggression and war in wanton violation of the sovereignty of other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. arrogance and their policy of aggression find their vivid manifestation in its moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK which has unswervingly held aloft the banner of independence and socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Workers' Party of Korea, basing itself on a deep analysis of the development of the times and the changed socio-class relations, set out the idea of placing the army before the working class for the first time in the history of the revolutionary movement and has pursued the unique Songun policy which calls for advancing the overall socialist construction on the principle of giving priority to military affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is precisely the reason why the WPK's Songun idea and politics display so tremendous attraction and vitality in the revolutionary practice with each passing day.

S. Korean Government Lambasted for Tarnishing June 15 Joint Declaration 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 13 (KCNA) -- The Reunification Solidarity of south Korea reportedly sponsored a rally in front of Kwanghwamun in Seoul on August 7 to oppose the U.S. moves for a war in the Korean peninsula and denounce the government for tarnishing the June 15 joint declaration.
 At the rally Vice-Chairman of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification Ri Kyu Jae, Permanent Co-representative of the Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration Kwon O Chang and other speakers said the June 15 spirit calls for settling the national issue independently by the concerted efforts of the Korean nation. Noting that the government was turning its back on national cooperation and clinging to south Korea-U.S. cooperation, they said this was obviously perfidy to the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stated they would launch a campaign for the resignation of the present government, condemning the authorities' crackdown on the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification, the South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification, the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils and the south Korean Council of Youth Organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 'Flailing the U.S. policy of isolating and stifling the north, they stressed that all the people should come out in smashing the U.S. imperialists' moves for a war and achieving reunification by the efforts of the Korean nation itself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution read out at the rally said the U.S. was entirely to blame for the war crisis on the Korean peninsula and the worsening south-north relations. It stated that the organization would wage a powerful struggle against the government's pro-American flunkeyist act in yielding to the U.S. pressure and dispatching troops and its anti-national behavior in impairing the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the rally, the protesters conducted information activities castigating the U.S. and the anti-reunification forces for intentionally worsening the south-north relations.

Friendly Meeting Held at Indonesian Embassy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 13 (KCNA) -- A friendly meeting was held at the Indonesian embassy here Thursday on the occasion of the 59th anniversary of the independence of Indonesia.
 Present on invitation were officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Barita Siburian, charge d' affaires ad interim, and officials of the embassy were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After appreciating Indonesian documentary films, the participants deepened friendly sentiments, chatting about developing the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries.

S. Korean Authorities Urged to Choose National Cooperation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 13 (KCNA) -- The (south) Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon) in a statement on August 7 demanded the south Korean authorities stop suppressing the pro-reunification patriotic forces and choose genuine national cooperation, according to a news report.
 The statement noted that the "government" authorities were persisting in criminal acts of barring national unity such as laying obstacles in the way of the reunification movement of patriotic organizations including the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification by anti-national and pro-U.S. acts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It stands out as an important matter in boosting national cooperation to remove the "enemy-benefiting" label from the patriotic organizations and ensure the freedom of the reunification movement, it said, adding: The "government" authorities should take the road to true national cooperation, not reading the face of the anti-reunification forces, depending on outsiders. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hanchongryon will totally shatter the authorities' anti-reunification and anti-national acts and surely achieve the freedom of the reunification movement and legalization of Hanchongryon, it declared.

U.S. and S. Korean Military's Evermore Undisguised Moves for War under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 13 (KCNA) -- The Central Committees of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea and the Korean Democratic Women's Union separately issued statements on August 12 denouncing the U.S. imperialists and the south Korean military for getting more frantic in their moves for a war of aggression against the north after working out "operation plan 5027-04," a new adventurous war scenario against it.
 They are going to stage "Ulji Focus Lens-04" joint military exercise targeted against the north as part of their moves to put the plan into practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The spokesman for the Central Committee of the federation branded "Ulji Focus Lens-04" projected by the U.S. and the south Korean bellicose forces as a test war and a preliminary war to be carried out under the pretext of "finally examining and improving" the preparations to cope with a war against the north with huge aggression forces in south Korea and overseas and south Korean administrative bodies involved. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expressed the expectation that the working class and other people of the world who aspire after justice, truth, peace and progress and progressive trade unions would take positive stand and measures against the U.S. bellicose forces' moves for a war of aggression against the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The spokesperson for the Central Committee of the union said the DPRK is fully ready to cope with any war methods in order to protect peace and security on the Korean peninsula, warning that if the U.S. imperialists and the south Korean warhawks persistently pursue a war of aggression despite the warning of the DPRK, they will drink a bitter cup of defeat in face of the war deterrent force built under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Should the U.S. imperialists ignite a war on this land at any cost, the people and women of the DPRK will join the People's Army, the strong revolutionary armed forces of Mt. Paektu, in wiping out the aggressors and provocateurs to the last man.

National Exhibition of Inventions and New Technologies Goes On
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 13 (KCNA) -- The 8th National Exhibition of Inventions and New Technologies is going on successfully at the Three-Revolution Exhibition in Pyongyang.
 The more than 1,000 exhibits displayed there are drawing attention of visitors including scientists and technicians for their great scientific and technical value. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are a mobile air plasma cutter, nickelchrome-nickelsilicon thermocouple K and micro-welder for solar battery.  The mobile air plasma cutter can cut metal material 30 mm thick at maximum. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It, equipped with a new kind of electrode, can operate in an oxidizable atmosphere and the cooling of the cutter and the formation of plasma are done by air pressure. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The nickelchrome-nickelsilicon thermocouple K is used as heatsensor element in low, middle and high temperature. It is safe like platinum at 1,300 degrees centigrade. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The micro-welder for solar battery can weld 0.05 micrometer silver sheet on 0.7 micrometer sheet of semiconductor.

Grand Monuments to National Liberation in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 13 (KCNA) -- The Arch of Triumph at the foot of Moran Hill in Pyongyang has been visited by many people with the approach of the 59th anniversary of the liberation of Korea.
 The arch was erected to convey to posterity the immortal exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung, who returned to Pyongyang in triumph after leading the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle to victory and achieving national liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many monuments have been built in different parts of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea to convey his feats to the generations to come. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Grand Monument on Mansu Hill was erected on the occasion of his 60th birth anniversary. It shows the whole course of the Korean revolution led by him and the undying feats performed by him in this course. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A grand monument is standing on Mt. Wangjae in Onsong, too. It tells that the President showed up in the Onsong area, put forward a strategic policy of expanding the anti-Japanese armed struggle to the homeland and aroused all the people of the country for its victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Monument to the Victorious Pochonbo Battle was erected in praise of the great victory won by the President in Pochonbo. He advanced into Pochonbo in June Juche 26 (1937) with the main unit of the Korean People's Revolutionary Army and dealt a heavy blow at the Japanese imperialists, demonstrating to the whole world that Korea was alive, not dead. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are the Grand Monument on Lake Samji and the Monument to the Victorious Battle in Musan Area. They represent the historical fact that in May 1939, he advanced into the homeland again and waged a victorious battle to instill the faith in national liberation in the hearts of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
They also show that only the armed struggle was the way out for the Korean people and only arms guarantee the victory of the Korean revolution.

Strengthening Driving Force for National Reunification Called for
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 13 (KCNA) -- The reunification of the country is for all the Koreans and it is their own cause. They are, therefore, a driving force of national reunification. Rodong Sinmun Friday says this in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No outside forces can replace the Korean nation in accomplishing the cause of national reunification. All Koreans should bear deep in mind that they are the master of the national reunification and fulfill their responsibility and role as such. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If they are to creditably perform them, they should firmly unite as one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The might of the driving force precisely means the might of unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Therefore the Korean nation should firmly unite as one. This is a sure guarantee for accomplishing the cause of national reunification. The great national unity should be achieved strictly on the principle of national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation should become the masters of national reunification and maintain the principle of solving the issue independently by the concerted efforts of the Koreans. This is the only way of attaining national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation should unite under the banner of patriotism and national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is one of the important ways for strengthening the driving force of national reunification to intensify solidarity and unity among the Koreans in the north and the south and overseas in the struggle for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Talking only is not enough to build the driving force of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This force comes into existence and grows strong only when all Koreans pool will and efforts and undertake joint actions to accomplish the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All Koreans in the north and the south and overseas should firmly unite under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration, a landmark for national reunification, to surely prevail over the anti-reunification forces and thus surely achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country without fail in the near future with the might of the driving force.
